<i>Sorry, I want to meditate.</i>

170
00:17:47,658 --> 00:17:49,148
<i>Sorry, sir?</i>

171
00:17:49,961 --> 00:17:52,657
<i>The revolution
is like a bicycle,</i>

172
00:17:53,398 --> 00:17:56,856
<i>if it stops, it falls down.</i>

173
00:18:03,074 --> 00:18:04,542
Sure?

174
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:06,169
Positive.

175
00:18:06,744 --> 00:18:09,304
I've been to the Congress.
The coup's a fact.

176
00:18:10,181 --> 00:18:12,046
Isabelita Perón will fall tonight.

177
00:18:17,288 --> 00:18:19,119
What are we waiting for?

178
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:25,018
Yes. Social exploitation,
the will to change. It's a fact!

179
00:18:26,364 --> 00:18:28,798
The Mulattos read the book.

180
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,633
I found a secondary contradiction.

181
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:34,330
While I burn,
you enjoy your hat.

182
00:18:38,442 --> 00:18:41,605
Stop it,
you underdeveloped savages!

183
00:18:41,979 --> 00:18:45,847
Never analize reality
like the ruling classes do.

184
00:18:46,450 --> 00:18:49,214
Rebel against Western culture!

185
00:18:49,487 --> 00:18:52,047
It's over!
Dad was right.

186
00:18:52,456 --> 00:18:55,584
Each people has
the government it deserves.

