192
00:19:24,421 --> 00:19:27,448
A new era has begun.

193
00:19:28,859 --> 00:19:32,727
An era with a very
clear objective...

194
00:19:33,264 --> 00:19:35,357
National Reorganization.

195
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:39,496
And the schools,
which cannot be islands...

196
00:19:39,570 --> 00:19:44,269
...will start their
own reorganization.

197
00:19:44,508 --> 00:19:46,601
The high schools...

198
00:19:46,711 --> 00:19:49,144
...will never again
become trade unions...

199
00:19:49,212 --> 00:19:51,271
or political committees.

200
00:19:51,514 --> 00:19:56,178
Schools will never
again encourage...

201
00:19:56,252 --> 00:20:00,587
...the diffusion of atheistic,
antinational ideas.

202
00:20:01,025 --> 00:20:02,856
I hope these words...

203
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,952
will serve as a calm,
but firm warning.

204
00:20:06,464 --> 00:20:08,364
That is all for now.

205
00:20:09,066 --> 00:20:11,227
Welcome to the new era...

206
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:13,360
of National Reorganization.

207
00:20:16,673 --> 00:20:18,800
Wonderful, Corchito.

208
00:20:35,059 --> 00:20:36,458
- Hi, Pablin.
- Hi.

209
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:39,394
A super hotdog from Panchito.

210
00:20:39,463 --> 00:20:41,226
Very funny!

211
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:43,557
No, thanks.
Too dangerous.

212
00:20:43,634 --> 00:20:46,227
You're kidding.
I'm an expert.

213
00:20:48,838 --> 00:20:50,567
Who's the blonde with Horacio?

214
00:20:51,007 --> 00:20:53,999
María Clara?
She's from Bahía Blanca.

215
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:57,445
She left cause things
were getting heavy.

216
00:20:57,814 --> 00:20:59,407
Don't spread it.

217
00:21:00,184 --> 00:21:01,811
Not bad, huh?

218
00:21:02,286 --> 00:21:03,844
Yeah.

219
00:21:07,091 --> 00:21:09,525
- I'm a lousy dancer.
- Me too.

220
00:21:09,694 --> 00:21:11,355
No, you're good.

221
00:21:11,862 --> 00:21:13,761
Don't believe him.

222
00:21:20,970 --> 00:21:22,835
What's your perfume?

223
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:26,231
Jasmin.

224
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:29,672
- What's so funny?
- Mom uses it.

225
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:31,476
I stole it from mine.

226
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:35,075
- Tell me something.
- Yes.

227
00:21:35,152 --> 00:21:37,814
Rememberthe meeting
about the pass?

228
00:21:38,355 --> 00:21:40,686
Why did you mention
the guerrilla?

229
00:21:41,691 --> 00:21:44,091
Just had to say something.

230
00:21:44,828 --> 00:21:47,490
You wouldn't let
anyone else speak.

231
00:21:47,864 --> 00:21:49,695
You wanted to be heroes.

232
00:21:49,766 --> 00:21:51,256
That's silly.

233
00:21:51,668 --> 00:21:53,932
But I did shock them.

234
00:22:00,644 --> 00:22:03,511
Look... don't I resemble Evita?

235
00:22:07,318 --> 00:22:10,013
Claudia, I like you a lot.

236
00:22:11,988 --> 00:22:13,819
No, Pablo.

237
00:22:16,626 --> 00:22:19,720
You're very nice, but no.

238
00:22:20,764 --> 00:22:22,732
Stop the music!

239
00:22:31,142 --> 00:22:33,702
- Let go, you beast!
- Keep still!

240
00:22:37,881 --> 00:22:40,315
- The bastards...
- Calm down.

241
00:23:00,770 --> 00:23:02,068
Darling...

242
00:23:04,741 --> 00:23:08,438
Be sensible.
Things are getting difficult.

243
00:23:08,945 --> 00:23:11,436
What am I supposed to do?

244
00:23:14,717 --> 00:23:19,177
I've been Mayor here.

245
00:23:19,389 --> 00:23:22,756
The military put me in prison.
I almost didn't make it.

246
00:23:23,159 --> 00:23:25,354
I know what I'm talking about.

247
00:23:25,962 --> 00:23:28,692
Stop sticking your head out.

248
00:23:29,532 --> 00:23:32,865
You can't ask me that.

249
00:23:33,970 --> 00:23:37,531
You've always said
one has to fight.

250
00:23:38,074 --> 00:23:41,669
I'm not asking you to give up...

251
00:23:42,312 --> 00:23:44,542
but don't be foolish.

252
00:23:44,881 --> 00:23:46,974
What then?

253
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:49,650
Should I take up embroidery?

254
00:24:05,835 --> 00:24:08,633
Don't rush things.

255
00:24:09,272 --> 00:24:11,103
You've got time.

256
00:24:11,541 --> 00:24:13,236
No, Dad.

257
00:24:13,910 --> 00:24:15,468
